[## LECTURE 4.8 — AUTOMATED MONTHLY AUDIT REPORT FOR THE EVIDENCE PACKAGE]

139
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Your auditor will want a human-readable monthly audit report.
Not just raw logs.
But a summary showing total queries processed, error rates,
any anomalies detected, and integrity verification status.

140
00:00:30,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Let me show you how to generate this report automatically.

141
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Create a script called generate-audit-report dot sh.
It takes year and month as arguments.
Defaults to the current year and month.

142
00:01:30,000 --> 00:02:00,000
First, pull the integrity report from S3.
aws s3 cp from the integrity-reports path.
If it exists, extract the status, total records, error count, error rate.

143
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Extract chain_valid, signatures_valid, and missing days.
Format these into a summary table.

144
00:02:30,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Second, list the S3 archive files for the month.
aws s3 ls on the audit-archive path.
Show each file with its size and last modified date.

145
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:30,000
Third, query CloudWatch for authentication failures in the month.
Use aws logs filter-log-events with filter pattern auth dot failure.
Count the events.

146
00:03:30,000 --> 00:04:00,000
Fourth, query the database for API key events.
Number of revocations in the month.
Number of new keys issued.

147
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Fifth, assemble the report in Markdown format.
Start with an executive summary table.
Include overall status, total queries, error rate, chain integrity, and S3 completeness.

148
00:04:30,000 --> 00:05:00,000
Add a section on hash chain integrity.
Describe the verification method.
Report the number of records verified and any broken chain.

149
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:30,000
Add a section on S3 archive status.
List all files with their sizes.
Show that every day of the month has an export.

150
00:05:30,000 --> 00:06:00,000
Add a section on access events.
Authentication failures, key revocations, and new keys issued.

151
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:30,000
Add a compliance controls status table.
CC7.5 for incident identification and response.
PI1.1 for processing integrity.
C1.1 for confidentiality.

152
00:06:30,000 --> 00:07:00,000
Finally, add a certification section.
The report was generated automatically.
All data is cryptographically verified.
Include the report ID and S3 archive location.

153
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:30,000
Save the report to soc2-evidence forward slash audit-reports.
Upload the report to the immutable evidence bucket with Object Lock.

154
00:07:30,000 --> 00:08:00,000
Run this script monthly, after the integrity verification is complete.
The report becomes part of your Type II evidence package.

